          <p>ðŸ”— <a href="https://github.com/grodowski/undercover">grodowski/undercover</a></p>
          <p>ðŸ”— <a href="https://github.com/grodowski/pronto-undercover">grodowski/pronto-undercover</a></p>
          <p>ðŸ”— <a href="https://github.com/nimblehq/danger-undercover">nimblehq/danger-undercover</a></p>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr/>

  <div>
    <h4 class="text-center my-4" >FAQ</h4>
    <p>
      <a class="lead" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse_1" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse_1">
        How do I pay?
      </a>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="collapse_1">
      <div class="card card-body mt-1 mb-3">
        You can pay for UndercoverCI with an accepted credit card (Discover, Visa, Mastercard, AMEX, Diner's Club) or PayPal. Subscriptions and payments are handled by Gumroad Inc. where you can access and modify your data as well as cancel anytime.
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      <a class="lead" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse_2" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse_2">
        Will I receive a VAT invoice?
      </a>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="collapse_2">
      <div class="card card-body mt-1 mb-3">
        <span><%= link_to "Yes", "https://customers.gumroad.com/article/194-i-need-an-invoice" %>.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      <a class="lead" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse_3" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse_3">
        How can I invite more users to use UndercoverCI?
      </a>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="collapse_3">
      <div class="card card-body mt-1 mb-3">
        A single subscription allows you to use UndercoverCI within a single GitHub organisation only. All members of your organisation gain access instantly once they sign in with the correct GitHub login.
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      <a class="lead" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse_4" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse_4">
        Which languages and SCMs are supported?
      </a>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="collapse_4">
      <div class="card card-body mt-1 mb-3">
        UncercoverCI is a dedicated GitHub integration which suports all Ruby and Ruby on Rails projects.
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      <a class="lead" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse_5" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse_5">
        Do I have to give access to my code?
      </a>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="collapse_5">
      <div class="card card-body mt-1 mb-3">
        <p>Yes. UndercoverCI will ask for the following GitHub permissions: Email address, Repository metadata (read-only), Repository contents (read-only), Checks (read and write).</p>

        <p>Look into the <code>undercover</code> gem and command-line tool for a self-hosted (and free) alternative.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      <a class="lead" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapse_6" role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapse_6">
        What if I am building open source?
      </a>
    </p>
    <div class="collapse" id="collapse_6">
      <div class="card card-body mt-1 mb-3">
        The service is free to use for public repositories. If you're an open source contributor you can use UndercoverCI free of charge.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
